The stylist not only attracts the models purely physically, but also designs the so-called product page in the journals (according to concrete specifications, for example, trend handbags, coats, etc.).
This is what the stylist and designer Mario Kameník told us about.
But that's not until Sunday.
This means that a stylist must have a good overall overview.
The Saturday lecture, filled with information about figure types, was spiced by three visitors from the industry:
by the stylist Jan Pokorný, the fashion designer Jakub Polanka and the fashion photographer Ben Renč.
Jakub reminded us that fashion is illusion and that a stylist should be able to exploit this.
And sent-in stylist is able to work with a single piece of clothing in very different ways.
The magic word is variability.
For example, you can wear a trench coat over the jeans as usual, like a T-shirt or coat, but you can also wear it on the naked body, put on your heel shoes and wear it as a dress.
It is enough to roll up the sleeves or the collar and the whole look looks very different.
"Play with it," he insisted.
But the following advice came to me the most: "First you have to know the rules perfectly."
"Only then can you hurt her," Jakub said.
Finally I realize why we have to tamper all these teachings, what you can combine with what and why, even if you often see completely different things in fashion journals.
Not to mention fashion shows.
Thanks to photographer Ben, I now know that a stylist must have prepared many more clothing variants than he ultimately photographs.
So you have to be prepared for a fashion story with ten pages (i.e. ten outfits) to style at least fifteen.
And also that the clothing in the photo in combination with other accessories sometimes looks very different than in reality.
So you have to expect all this in the design of the outfit.
Jan Pokorný also confirmed to us that image and style sometimes account for half of the success.
You just need Madonna, a not exactly brilliant singer, who has made a world star out of image and marketing.
In the Czech Republic, the services of a stylist are more reserved.
Even well-known personalities often consider this to be thrown out money (the main thing is that I bring something, how I look is secondary).
And if anyone of us is already styling, then we should expect that he or she will most likely impose a very different (smaller) size on us than he or she really needs.
Then you only have to Google to determine with certainty that the tabloid press writes that the corresponding celebrity has closed or decreased again, etc.
Jan and Mario advised us on Sunday not to believe that a stylist only needs to focus on fashion and then "assemble" the outfit.
In his work, he must above all communicate with the people he styles and he must be a smart psychologist.
Assess people without showing off and standing by their opinion.
"If any manager orders us to see her closet and to add pretty pieces, then we can't clean out and tell her the whole closet - my God, that's terrible."
"You have to find at least a few commendable things to which you recommend what you can wear to it," Mario says.
He also showed us very concretely what such a so-called "place bag" must contain.
So such a bag, which you button at the waist and in which you carry all the necessary proprieties with you.
In addition to such clear things, such as scissors, hair removal rollers or safety pins, it also contains such utensils as a nylon thread (so the stylist helps to photograph products, such as handbags or hats), special clips with which the clothes are gathered at the back if it is too large (plugs or other clamps are prohibited so that the fabric does not break) and of course sewing stuff.
But in order for us not only to have to listen, but also to try something practically, we learned how to properly undergue shoes.
