Thus, under the following conditions, the votes contained in one or more electoral packages may not be partially counted The results in the minutes do not match; the record of the counting and calculation of votes is not available in terms of file or it is not in the possession of the chairman of the election committee or there are obvious errors or amendments in the minutes.
In addition, the total counting of the fully completed voting slips can be made if there is a difference between the presumed winner and the one in second place, which is equal to or less than one percent, provided that at the beginning of the session there is an explicit request from the party or. Coalition chairwoman, who is the second of the candidates mentioned.
The counting of votes can also be carried out in their entirety if, after completion of the ordinary calculation, it is established that the difference between the presumed winner and the candidate in second place is equal to or less than one percent, provided that there is an explicit request from a representative of the party whose candidate has become second. In this case, the election packages that have been suspended from a partial count would be excluded.
