The squatters, who had occupied 11 of the building's 13 apartments - the rest were inhabited - took the entire electrical facility and part of the water supply with them. In addition, they had painted the walls and left behind all kinds of garbage, especially cans of alcoholic beverages.
In the three lower floors, huge parties were celebrated, which lasted up to two days and drove the tenants to despair.
Next to the building is a nightclub, Balmes 51, which also suffered damage from it.
Her owner, Maria Pantinat, explained to Europa Press that her business would have declined by 80% since the start of the squat.
