The Guardia Urbana (urban police) also confirmed that it has received more complaints from its neighbours in recent weeks.
The chairman of the PP (Partido Popular - People's Party) in Barcelona's city council, Alberto Fernández Díaz, had last week called for the building to be cleared immediately and to get a grip on the problems of bourgeois coexistence as well as the coming down of the district.
