In Chernobyl, the drama was conjured up by reactor construction as well as inend-custom, human error.
At Fukushima, some seem to forget that the accident was caused by two natural disasters of unprecedented proportions that caused the deaths of several tens of thousands of people.
The nuclear industry will draw its lessons from this accident as much as it had done after the two preceding ones.
